<h1>Job Overview</h1>

<h2>General Responsibilities:</h2>

<p>Our positions include semi-skilled and skilled technical,
theatrical work in implementing staging and lighting, audio/visual,
and other related work. Employees are expected to use professional expertise,
discretion, and judgment in completing a wide range of assignments.
Under general supervision, employees are expected to work independently within established parameters. </p>

<h2>Road Crew:</h2>

<p>We offer opportunities to travel out of state to provide staging support for various events.
Travel time and work type are based upon client needs. Transportation, hotels, & per diem provided.
More info is available upon request.</p>

<h2>Duties & Responsibilities</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Perform work as audio/visual technicians, stage carpenters, stage electricians, riggers, spotlight operators, truck loaders, and set up/tear down for concerts, theater, and other events.</li>
  <li>Ensure that all safety regulations and work rules are followed.</li>
</ul>

