<h1>Qualifications</h1>

<ul>
  <li>Working knowledge of the tools and materials and working knowledge
  of the methods and practices used in the general installation, testing,
  operation, and removal of theatrical staging, sound,
  and lighting associated with the entertainment industry</li>
  <li>Working knowledge of theatrical production terms and techniques</li>
  <li>Working knowledge of equipment parts and components</li>
  <li>Working knowledge of occupational hazards and necessary safety procedures and equipment</li>
  <li>Ability to communicate effectively</li>
  <li>Ability to manage time effectively and work under tight deadlines </li>
  <li>Ability to work with others as a team</li>
  <li>Ability to lift 25 pounds repeatedly, 50-70 pounds frequently, and heavier on a limited basis</li>
  <li>Ability to bend, twist, stoop, climb ladders, work from heights and perform other manual labor tasks</li>
</ul>

